CMC Capital Partners to raise $1b China media fund


















Winnie Liu



					12 October 2015
				






Tweet
 




Facebook
 




LinkedIn
 




Google plus
 




Save this article
 




Send to
 












								China’s CMC Capital Partners, a private equity firm set up by Ruigang Li, formerly president of Shanghai Media Group (SMG), is looking to raise $1 billion for a media-focused fund. 

							



                        		
                        		
                        		The fund comprises two vehicles, one US dollar-denominated fund and the renminbi-denominated, according to people familiar with the situation. The investment strategy for Fund II is largely consistent...
                        	

















